<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <% var pageTitle = state.name + ' Income Tax Calculator 2025 | MyTaxCalcs'; %>
  <% var metaDesc = state.hasIncomeTax
    ? 'Free ' + state.name + ' income tax calculator for 2025. Estimate state and federal income tax, effective rate, and take-home pay. Includes ' + state.name + ' tax brackets and a worked example.'
    : state.name + ' has no state income tax. Use our free calculator to estimate your federal income tax as a ' + state.name + ' resident for 2025.'; %>
  <title><%= pageTitle %></title>
  <meta name="description" content="<%= metaDesc %>">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://mytaxcalcs.com/<%= state.slug %>-income-tax-calculator">
  <meta property="og:title" content="<%= pageTitle %>">
  <meta property="og:description" content="<%= metaDesc %>">
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://mytaxcalcs.com/<%= state.slug %>-income-tax-calculator">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <meta property="og:site_name" content="MyTaxCalcs">
  <meta property="og:image" content="https://mytaxcalcs.com/images/og-default.png">
  <meta property="og:image:width" content="1200">
  <meta property="og:image:height" content="630">
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
  <meta name="twitter:title" content="<%= pageTitle %>">
  <meta name="twitter:description" content="<%= metaDesc %>">
  <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://mytaxcalcs.com/images/og-default.png">
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="any">
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml">
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/favicon.png">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-FS9HCDT0D7"></script>
  <script>window.dataLayer=window.dataLayer||[];function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}gtag('js',new Date());gtag('config','G-FS9HCDT0D7');</script>
  <script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5193834725888549" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <style>
    .state-overview-section{background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem 1.75rem;margin:1.5rem 0}
    .state-overview-section h2{font-size:1.2rem;color:#111827;margin-bottom:.75rem}
    .state-overview-section p{color:#374151;line-height:1.7;margin:0}
    .key-facts-bar{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1px;background:#e5e7eb;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;margin:1.5rem 0 2rem}
    .fact-item{flex:1 1 160px;background:#fff;padding:1rem 1.25rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.25rem}
    .fact-label{font-size:.75rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;color:#6b7280}
    .fact-value{font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827}
    .fact-value a{font-size:.85rem;font-weight:600;color:#16a34a;text-decoration:none}
    .fact-value a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
    .bracket-section{margin:2rem 0}
    .bracket-section h2{font-size:1.3rem;color:#111827;margin-bottom:.5rem}
    .bracket-section>p{color:#4b5563;margin-bottom:1rem}
    .bracket-table-wrap{overflow-x:auto;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb}
    .bracket-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.95rem}
    .bracket-table thead{background:#16a34a;color:#fff}
    .bracket-table thead th{padding:.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;font-weight:600}
    .bracket-table tbody tr:nth-child(even){background:#f9fafb}
    .bracket-table tbody tr:hover{background:#f0fdf4}
    .bracket-table tbody td{padding:.65rem 1rem;color:#111827;border-bottom:1px solid #f3f4f6}
    .bracket-note{font-size:.8rem;color:#6b7280;margin-top:.5rem}
    .bracket-note a{color:#16a34a}
    .flat-rate-callout{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1rem;background:#f0fdf4;border:2px solid #16a34a;border-radius:12px;padding:1.25rem 1.75rem;margin:1rem 0}
    .flat-rate-number{font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;color:#16a34a;line-height:1}
    .flat-rate-label{font-size:1rem;color:#374151;font-weight:500}
    .no-tax-callout-section{margin:1.5rem 0}
    .no-tax-callout{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:1rem;background:#f0fdf4;border:2px solid #16a34a;border-radius:12px;padding:1.25rem 1.75rem;margin-bottom:1rem}
    .no-tax-icon{font-size:1.75rem;color:#16a34a;font-weight:800;line-height:1;flex-shrink:0}
    .no-tax-callout h2{font-size:1.15rem;color:#111827;margin:0 0 .35rem}
    .no-tax-callout p{color:#374151;margin:0}
    .no-tax-callout-section>p{color:#4b5563;margin-top:.75rem}
    .worked-example-section{margin:2rem 0}
    .worked-example-section h2{font-size:1.3rem;color:#111827;margin-bottom:.5rem}
    .worked-example-section>p{color:#4b5563;margin-bottom:1rem}
    .example-box{border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden}
    .example-scenario{background:#f9fafb;padding:.75rem 1.25rem;font-size:.9rem;color:#374151;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb}
    .example-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.9rem}
    .example-table th{background:#f3f4f6;padding:.6rem 1.25rem;text-align:left;font-weight:600;color:#374151;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb}
    .example-table th:last-child,.example-table td:last-child{text-align:right}
    .example-table td{padding:.6rem 1.25rem;color:#111827;border-bottom:1px solid #f3f4f6}
    .example-table tfoot td{background:#f0fdf4;font-weight:700;color:#15803d;border-top:2px solid #bbf7d0}
    .state-faq-section{margin:2rem 0}
    .state-faq-section h2{font-size:1.3rem;color:#111827;margin-bottom:1rem}
    .state-faq-item{border-bottom:1px solid #f3f4f6;padding:1rem 0}
    .state-faq-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
    .state-faq-item h3{font-size:1rem;font-weight:600;color:#111827;margin:0 0 .4rem}
    .state-faq-item p{color:#4b5563;margin:0;line-height:1.65}
    .state-faq-item a{color:#16a34a}
    .ri-value.green{color:#16a34a}
    .ri-value.red{color:#dc2626}
    @media(max-width:600px){
      .key-facts-bar{flex-direction:column;gap:0}
      .fact-item{border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb}
      .flat-rate-callout{flex-direction:column;gap:.5rem}
      .no-tax-callout{flex-direction:column}
    }
  </style>
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebApplication",
    "name": "<%= state.name %> Income Tax Calculator 2025",
    "description": "<%= metaDesc %>",
    "url": "https://mytaxcalcs.com/<%= state.slug %>-income-tax-calculator",
    "applicationCategory": "FinanceApplication",
    "operatingSystem": "Web",
    "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
    "provider": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "MyTaxCalcs", "url": "https://mytaxcalcs.com" }
  }
  </script>
</head>
<body>

  <header class="site-header">
    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <span class="logo-mark">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <rect x="1" y="1" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e"/>
            <rect x="11" y="1" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.5"/>
            <rect x="1" y="11" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.5"/>
            <rect x="11" y="11" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.25"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <span class="logo-text">MyTaxCalcs</span>
      </a>
      <ul class="nav-links">
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="/calculators">Calculators</a></li>
        <li><a href="/states">States</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog">Blog</a></li>
        <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
        <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="calc-page">

    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span class="breadcrumb-sep">›</span>
      <a href="/states">States</a>
      <span class="breadcrumb-sep">›</span>
      <span><%= state.name %> Income Tax Calculator</span>
    </nav>

    <div class="calc-page-header">
      <div class="page-eyebrow"><%= state.abbr %> State Tax</div>
      <h1><%= state.name %> Income Tax Calculator</h1>
      <% if (state.hasIncomeTax) { %>
        <p>Estimate your 2025 <%= state.name %> state and federal income tax. Includes <%= state.name %> tax brackets, a worked dollar example, and filing tips.</p>
      <% } else { %>
        <p><%= state.name %> has no state income tax. Use this calculator to estimate your federal income tax as a <%= state.name %> resident for 2025.</p>
      <% } %>
    </div>

    <div class="ad-zone">
      <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
      <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549" data-ad-slot="4212978293" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
      <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
    </div>

    <section class="key-facts-bar">
      <div class="fact-item">
        <span class="fact-label">State Income Tax</span>
        <span class="fact-value"><%= state.hasIncomeTax ? state.brackets : 'None' %></span>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-item">
        <span class="fact-label">Top Rate</span>
        <span class="fact-value"><%= state.hasIncomeTax ? state.topRate + '%' : '0%' %></span>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-item">
        <span class="fact-label">Tax Type</span>
        <span class="fact-value">
          <% if (!state.hasIncomeTax) { %>No Income Tax<% } else if (state.topRate === state.bottomRate) { %>Flat Rate<% } else { %>Graduated<% } %>
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-item">
        <span class="fact-label">Official Source</span>
        <span class="fact-value"><a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a></span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="state-overview-section">
      <h2><%= state.name %> State Income Tax Overview</h2>
      <p><%= state.overview %></p>
    </section>

    <% if (state.hasIncomeTax && state.bracketRows && state.bracketRows.length > 0) { %>
    <section class="bracket-section">
      <h2><%= state.name %> Income Tax Brackets (2025)</h2>
      <p>These are the <%= state.name %> state income tax brackets for single filers. Only the income within each bracket is taxed at that rate — not your entire income.</p>
      <div class="bracket-table-wrap">
        <table class="bracket-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Taxable Income</th><th>Tax Rate</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <% state.bracketRows.forEach(function(row) { %>
            <tr>
              <td><% if (row.max === null) { %>Over $<%= row.min.toLocaleString() %><% } else { %>$<%= row.min.toLocaleString() %> – $<%= row.max.toLocaleString() %><% } %></td>
              <td><%= row.rate %>%</td>
            </tr>
            <% }); %>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="bracket-note">Source: <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a>. Brackets shown are for single filers. Married filing jointly thresholds may differ.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="worked-example-section">
      <h2>What a <%= state.name %> Resident Actually Pays: A Worked Example</h2>
      <p>Your effective tax rate is almost always lower than your top bracket. Here is the math for a single filer earning $65,000.</p>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-scenario"><strong>Scenario:</strong> Single filer, $65,000 in taxable income</div>
        <div id="worked-example-output"></div>
      </div>
      <script>
      (function() {
        var brackets = <%- JSON.stringify(state.bracketRows) %>;
        var income = 65000;
        var tax = 0;
        var rows = [];
        for (var i = 0; i < brackets.length; i++) {
          var b = brackets[i];
          if (income <= b.min) break;
          var upper = b.max === null ? income : Math.min(b.max, income);
          var chunk = upper - b.min;
          var amount = chunk * (b.rate / 100);
          tax += amount;
          rows.push({ rate: b.rate, chunk: chunk, amount: amount });
        }
        var effectiveRate = (tax / income * 100).toFixed(1);
        var fmt = function(n) { return '$' + n.toLocaleString('en-US', {minimumFractionDigits:2, maximumFractionDigits:2}); };
        var html = '<table class="example-table"><thead><tr><th>Bracket</th><th>Income in Bracket</th><th>Tax</th></tr></thead><tbody>';
        rows.forEach(function(r) {
          html += '<tr><td>' + r.rate + '%</td><td>' + fmt(r.chunk) + '</td><td>' + fmt(r.amount) + '</td></tr>';
        });
        html += '</tbody><tfoot>';
        html += '<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Total State Tax on $65,000</strong></td><td><strong>' + fmt(tax) + '</strong></td></tr>';
        html += '<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Effective State Tax Rate</strong></td><td><strong>' + effectiveRate + '%</strong></td></tr>';
        html += '</tfoot></table>';
        document.getElementById('worked-example-output').innerHTML = html;
      })();
      </script>
    </section>

    <% } else if (state.hasIncomeTax && state.topRate === state.bottomRate) { %>
    <section class="bracket-section">
      <h2><%= state.name %> Income Tax Rate (2025)</h2>
      <p><%= state.name %> uses a flat income tax rate — the same percentage applies to all taxable income regardless of how much you earn.</p>
      <div class="flat-rate-callout">
        <span class="flat-rate-number"><%= state.topRate %>%</span>
        <span class="flat-rate-label">Flat rate on all taxable income</span>
      </div>
      <p class="bracket-note">Source: <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a></p>
    </section>
    <section class="worked-example-section">
      <h2>What a <%= state.name %> Resident Actually Pays: A Worked Example</h2>
      <div class="example-box">
        <div class="example-scenario"><strong>Scenario:</strong> Single filer, $65,000 in taxable income</div>
        <table class="example-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Taxable Income</td><td>$65,000.00</td></tr>
            <tr><td><%= state.name %> Flat Rate</td><td><%= state.topRate %>%</td></tr>
          </tbody>
          <tfoot>
            <tr><td><strong>Estimated State Tax</strong></td><td><strong>$<%= (650 * state.topRate).toFixed(2) %></strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Effective Rate</strong></td><td><strong><%= state.topRate %>%</strong></td></tr>
          </tfoot>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <% } else { %>
    <section class="no-tax-callout-section">
      <div class="no-tax-callout">
        <div class="no-tax-icon">✓</div>
        <div>
          <h2><%= state.name %> Has No State Income Tax</h2>
          <p><%= state.noTaxNote %></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>As a <%= state.name %> resident, your state income tax is $0. The calculator below estimates your <strong>federal</strong> income tax, which applies to all U.S. residents regardless of state.</p>
    </section>
    <% } %>

    <div class="calc-card-form">
      <h2>Estimate Your <%= state.hasIncomeTax ? state.name + ' + ' : '' %>Federal Income Tax</h2>
      <div class="form-grid">
        <div class="form-field full">
          <label>Gross Annual Income</label>
          <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span><input type="number" id="s-income" placeholder="0" min="0"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-field">
          <label>Filing Status</label>
          <select id="s-status">
            <option value="single">Single</option>
            <option value="mfj">Married Filing Jointly</option>
            <option value="mfs">Married Filing Separately</option>
            <option value="hoh">Head of Household</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="form-field">
          <label>Deduction Type</label>
          <select id="s-ded-type">
            <option value="standard">Standard Deduction</option>
            <option value="itemized">Itemized Deduction</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="form-field full" id="s-itemized-wrap" style="display:none">
          <label>Itemized Deduction Amount</label>
          <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span><input type="number" id="s-itemized" placeholder="0" min="0"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-field">
          <label>Federal Tax Withheld</label>
          <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span><input type="number" id="s-withheld" placeholder="0" min="0"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-field">
          <label>Tax Credits</label>
          <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span><input type="number" id="s-credits" placeholder="0" min="0"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="form-actions">
        <button class="btn-calc" id="s-calc-btn">Calculate Tax Estimate</button>
      </div>
      <div id="s-results" style="display:none">
        <div class="result-card">
          <div class="result-card-header">
            <div class="result-icon">📊</div>
            <h2>Your Tax Estimate</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="result-primary">
            <div class="result-grid">
              <div class="result-item"><span class="ri-label">Gross Income</span><span class="ri-value" id="r-gross">—</span></div>
              <div class="result-item"><span class="ri-label">Deduction</span><span class="ri-value" id="r-ded">—</span></div>
              <div class="result-item"><span class="ri-label">Federal Taxable Income</span><span class="ri-value" id="r-taxable">—</span></div>
              <div class="result-item"><span class="ri-label">Federal Income Tax</span><span class="ri-value" id="r-fed">—</span></div>
              <% if (state.hasIncomeTax) { %>
              <div class="result-item"><span class="ri-label"><%= state.name %> State Tax (Est.)</span><span class="ri-value" id="r-state">—</span></div>
              <% } %>
              <div class="result-item"><span class="ri-label">Marginal Federal Rate</span><span class="ri-value" id="r-marginal">—</span></div>
              <div class="result-item"><span class="ri-label">Effective Federal Rate</span><span class="ri-value" id="r-effective">—</span></div>
              <div class="result-item"><span class="ri-label">Estimated Refund / Owed</span><span class="ri-value" id="r-refund">—</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script>
      document.getElementById('s-ded-type').addEventListener('change', function() {
        document.getElementById('s-itemized-wrap').style.display = this.value === 'itemized' ? 'block' : 'none';
      });
      document.getElementById('s-calc-btn').addEventListener('click', function() {
        var gross    = parseFloat(document.getElementById('s-income').value) || 0;
        var status   = document.getElementById('s-status').value;
        var dedType  = document.getElementById('s-ded-type').value;
        var itemized = parseFloat(document.getElementById('s-itemized').value) || 0;
        var withheld = parseFloat(document.getElementById('s-withheld').value) || 0;
        var credits  = parseFloat(document.getElementById('s-credits').value) || 0;
        var stdDed = {single:15000,mfj:30000,mfs:15000,hoh:22500};
        var ded = dedType === 'itemized' ? itemized : stdDed[status];
        var taxable = Math.max(0, gross - ded);
        var brackets = {
          single:[[11925,.10],[48475,.12],[103350,.22],[197300,.24],[250525,.32],[626350,.35],[Infinity,.37]],
          mfj:[[23850,.10],[96950,.12],[206700,.22],[394600,.24],[501050,.32],[751600,.35],[Infinity,.37]],
          mfs:[[11925,.10],[48475,.12],[103350,.22],[197300,.24],[250525,.32],[375800,.35],[Infinity,.37]],
          hoh:[[17000,.10],[64850,.12],[103350,.22],[197300,.24],[250500,.32],[626350,.35],[Infinity,.37]]
        };
        var fedTax = 0, margRate = .10, prev = 0;
        var bkts = brackets[status];
        for (var i = 0; i < bkts.length; i++) {
          if (taxable <= prev) break;
          var chunk = Math.min(taxable, bkts[i][0]) - prev;
          fedTax += chunk * bkts[i][1];
          margRate = bkts[i][1];
          prev = bkts[i][0];
        }
        fedTax = Math.max(0, fedTax - credits);
        var effectiveRate = gross > 0 ? (fedTax / gross * 100).toFixed(1) : '0.0';
        var refund = withheld - fedTax;
        <% if (state.hasIncomeTax) { %>
        var stateTax = 0;
        <% if (state.bracketRows && state.bracketRows.length > 0) { %>
        var sb = <%- JSON.stringify(state.bracketRows) %>;
        for (var j = 0; j < sb.length; j++) {
          if (taxable <= sb[j].min) break;
          var sUpper = sb[j].max === null ? taxable : Math.min(sb[j].max, taxable);
          stateTax += (sUpper - sb[j].min) * (sb[j].rate / 100);
        }
        <% } else { %>
        stateTax = taxable * (<%= state.topRate %> / 100);
        <% } %>
        <% } %>
        var fmt = function(v) { return '$' + v.toLocaleString('en-US', {minimumFractionDigits:2,maximumFractionDigits:2}); };
        document.getElementById('r-gross').textContent = fmt(gross);
        document.getElementById('r-ded').textContent = fmt(ded);
        document.getElementById('r-taxable').textContent = fmt(taxable);
        document.getElementById('r-fed').textContent = fmt(fedTax);
        <% if (state.hasIncomeTax) { %>
        document.getElementById('r-state').textContent = fmt(stateTax);
        <% } %>
        document.getElementById('r-marginal').textContent = (margRate*100).toFixed(0) + '%';
        document.getElementById('r-effective').textContent = effectiveRate + '%';
        var rEl = document.getElementById('r-refund');
        rEl.textContent = (refund >= 0 ? 'Refund: ' : 'Owed: ') + fmt(Math.abs(refund));
        rEl.className = 'ri-value ' + (refund >= 0 ? 'green' : 'red');
        document.getElementById('s-results').style.display = 'block';
      });
    </script>

    <div class="ad-zone">
      <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
      <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549" data-ad-slot="5205436277" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
      <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
    </div>

    <section class="state-faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions — <%= state.name %> Income Tax</h2>
      <% if (state.hasIncomeTax) { %>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>Does <%= state.name %> have a state income tax?</h3>
        <p>Yes. <%= state.name %> imposes a state income tax with a <%= state.topRate === state.bottomRate ? 'flat rate of ' + state.topRate + '%' : 'top marginal rate of ' + state.topRate + '%' %>. This is separate from your federal income tax obligation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>What is the <%= state.name %> income tax rate for 2025?</h3>
        <p><% if (state.topRate === state.bottomRate) { %><%= state.name %> uses a flat income tax rate of <%= state.topRate %>% on all taxable income, regardless of income level or filing status.<% } else { %><%= state.name %> uses a graduated income tax system with rates ranging from <%= state.bottomRate %>% to <%= state.topRate %>%. Only the income within each bracket is taxed at that rate — not your entire income.<% } %></p>
      </div>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>Do I have to file a <%= state.name %> state tax return?</h3>
        <p>Most full-year <%= state.name %> residents with income above the state filing threshold must file a state return. Check the <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a> for current thresholds and requirements.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>How accurate is this <%= state.name %> state tax estimate?</h3>
        <p>This is a planning estimate. The state result uses <%= state.name %>'s published brackets but does not account for all state deductions, credits, exemptions, or local taxes. Verify your actual liability with official <%= state.name %> tax forms or a qualified tax professional.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>Does this calculator include federal income tax?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Results show both your estimated <%= state.name %> state income tax and your federal income tax using 2025 federal brackets — so you can see your full combined picture in one place.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>Where can I find official <%= state.name %> tax forms?</h3>
        <p>Official forms, instructions, and filing guidance are available at the <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a>.</p>
      </div>
      <% } else { %>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>Does <%= state.name %> have a state income tax?</h3>
        <p>No. <%= state.name %> does not impose a broad-based state income tax on wages, salaries, or most personal income. <%= state.noTaxNote %></p>
      </div>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>Do I still owe federal income tax as a <%= state.name %> resident?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Federal income tax applies to all U.S. residents regardless of state. <%= state.name %> residents pay the same federal brackets as everyone else — only your state income tax liability is $0.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>What taxes do <%= state.name %> residents pay instead of income tax?</h3>
        <p><%= state.overview.substring(0, 350) %>...</p>
      </div>
      <div class="state-faq-item">
        <h3>Do I need to file a <%= state.name %> state tax return?</h3>
        <p><%= state.name %> does not require a personal income tax return for most residents. You must still file a federal return with the IRS. Check the <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a> for any state-specific obligations that may apply.</p>
      </div>
      <% } %>
    </section>

